! $Id: match,v 1.1 2001/12/07 16:54:15 toast Exp $
MATCH(pattern wordlist)
  Returns the index of the first word in wordlist that matches the
  pattern.  The first word in wordlist has index 1.

Examples:
  match(m* marble oak mantle)	- Returns 1
  match(m*n* marble oak mantle)	- Returns 3

See also:
  FUNCTIONS RMATCH
